parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can result in the airbags not deploying in the event of a crash, which can lead to serious injury or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag light stays on
the airbag strap comes undone
the clock spring on the airbag fractures
none of the airbags deploy in the event of a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag module can cause the airbag light to stay on, indicating that the airbags are disabled and will not deploy in the event of a crash, which can lead to serious injury or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag light stays on
the airbag module is faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clock spring can cause the airbag to malfunction, which can lead to serious injury or fatalities in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The clock spring on the airbag fractures.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can result in serious injury or fatalities.
symptoms: None of the airbags deploy in the event of a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates without warning
the brake pedal requires extreme force to stop the vehicle
unintended acceleration occurs at low speeds (under 15 mph).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cruise control malfunction can cause unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and accidents.
symptoms: The cruise control malfunctions
the vehicle accelerates without warning
the G4 sensor needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of dashboard lights can cause distraction, confusion, and decreased visibility while driving, potentially leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Dashboard lights suddenly turn off while driving
especially at night
and may return on their own after a short period; recurring instances of dashboard light failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the horn can lead to reduced safety and increased risk of accidents, as the driver may be unable to alert other road users in emergency situations.
symptoms: The horn fails to operate occasionally
especially in cold temperatures; the horn may work most of the time
but not always; the failure is often intermittent and unpredictable.
